WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:11.120
His family name is Edson Arrantes Donasciemento, but people call him Halé.

00:11.120 --> 00:16.000
He is the number one player in the story of soccer.

00:16.000 --> 00:26.000
In 1363 games, he scored 1264 goals.

00:26.000 --> 00:31.200
At Brazil, he won the World Cup three times.

00:31.200 --> 00:37.320
He visited 88 countries, and his picture was in every newspaper.

00:37.320 --> 00:42.480
But, Halé is not only a famous soccer player.

00:42.480 --> 00:48.600
He knows Spanish, Italian, English, and French.

00:48.600 --> 00:54.120
He writes music, and he works for the Brazilian government.

00:54.360 --> 00:57.960
Today, Halé is famous.

00:57.960 --> 01:04.600
In 1950, he was a boy of 10 with no shoes.

01:04.600 --> 01:07.960
This is his story.

01:07.960 --> 01:11.000
Early years.

01:11.000 --> 01:20.600
Edson Arrantes Donasciemento came into the world on the night of October 23, 1940.

01:20.600 --> 01:23.960
His family called him Dico.

01:23.960 --> 01:30.200
They lived in a small house in Tres Corsois, Brazil.

01:30.200 --> 01:35.480
Dico has soccer players' legs, his father said.

01:35.480 --> 01:39.720
He's going to be a doctor, not a soccer player.

01:39.720 --> 01:42.920
Dico's mother Celeste said.

01:42.920 --> 01:46.200
Celeste was angry.

01:46.280 --> 01:53.880
Don Dino, Dico's father, was a soccer player, but he didn't make much money.

01:53.880 --> 01:56.280
Don Dino smiled.

01:56.280 --> 02:04.040
There were problems in the family about soccer, but there was a lot of love in the house too.

02:04.040 --> 02:11.320
In 1944, the manager of Baru Athletico, a big soccer club,

02:11.320 --> 02:13.320
talked to Don Dino.

02:13.320 --> 02:17.960
"'We want a good soccer player,' the man said.

02:17.960 --> 02:23.160
"'It's not much money, but there's work in the town too.'

02:23.160 --> 02:26.440
"'Do you want the job?'

02:26.440 --> 02:32.440
Don Dino said yes, and the family moved to Baru.

02:32.440 --> 02:35.880
The manager was wrong about one thing.

02:35.880 --> 02:40.200
There was no work for Don Dino in the town.

02:40.280 --> 02:47.000
He only played soccer, and the family had the same money problems.

02:47.000 --> 02:52.120
But Dico was happy in Baru with his new friends.

02:52.120 --> 02:57.720
They played their first game of soccer in Rua Rubens Aruda,

02:57.720 --> 03:00.360
a street near Dico's house.

03:00.360 --> 03:05.720
Their football was an old newspaper.

03:05.800 --> 03:09.480
Little Dico played a lot of soccer.

03:09.480 --> 03:12.600
Celeste wasn't happy about this.

03:12.600 --> 03:18.280
"'There's no money in the game,' she said,' Dico smiled.

03:18.280 --> 03:20.440
His mother was right.

03:20.440 --> 03:25.800
He loved soccer, but he didn't want to be a soccer player.

03:25.800 --> 03:29.240
He wanted to work at the airport.

03:29.240 --> 03:33.640
He often went there and looked at the airplanes.

03:33.640 --> 03:39.720
But Dico's first job wasn't in a soccer stadium or an airport.

03:39.720 --> 03:44.840
It was at Baru Station in 1948.

03:44.840 --> 03:47.400
He cleaned shoes.

03:47.400 --> 03:52.120
In that year, things were difficult for the family.

03:52.120 --> 03:57.480
But then, Don Dino started work in a doctor's office.

03:57.480 --> 04:02.120
He cleaned the building and answered the telephone.

04:02.120 --> 04:08.360
In the afternoons, Dico often visited his father.

04:08.360 --> 04:15.480
"'In ten years, you're going to be a young man,' Don Dino said one day.

04:15.480 --> 04:18.920
"'What do you want to do?'

04:18.920 --> 04:23.400
"'I want to work with airplanes,' Dico said.

04:23.400 --> 04:30.760
"'Okay, but school is important for that,' said his father.

04:30.760 --> 04:34.680
Later that year, Dico started school.

04:34.680 --> 04:37.560
He was the good student.

04:37.560 --> 04:43.400
He only stayed in school because he wanted a job at the airport.

04:43.400 --> 04:48.680
But one day, an airplane came down near the school.

04:48.680 --> 04:55.480
Dico and his friends went to the doctor's office and looked in one of the windows.

04:55.480 --> 04:59.960
The man from the airplane was dead.

05:00.040 --> 05:04.840
Dico never talked about a job with airplanes again.

05:04.840 --> 05:08.520
A new name.

05:08.520 --> 05:12.840
The important thing for Dico now was soccer.

05:12.840 --> 05:17.320
Evenings and weekends, he played with his friends.

05:17.320 --> 05:21.880
In the afternoons, he was with Don Dino.

05:21.880 --> 05:29.560
Don Dino was his soccer teacher and Dico was a very good student.

05:29.560 --> 05:35.560
After two years, Dico was the number one young player in Baru.

05:35.560 --> 05:41.240
His friends started to call him Pele.

05:41.240 --> 05:45.400
"'Where does the name come from?' people often ask.

05:45.400 --> 05:48.360
Pele doesn't know.

05:48.360 --> 05:57.000
In 1951, Pele started a club, September 7, with his friends.

05:57.080 --> 06:01.880
People called them the team with no shoes.

06:01.880 --> 06:07.880
They wanted to play in Baru Atletico's championship for young teams.

06:07.880 --> 06:11.080
But the shoes were a problem.

06:11.080 --> 06:17.960
One day, a father of one of the players came with shoes for the team.

06:17.960 --> 06:21.880
"'Today, I'm giving you a new name.

06:21.960 --> 06:25.160
Américino,' he said.

06:25.160 --> 06:31.080
"'Now they can't call you the team with no shoes.'

06:31.080 --> 06:37.560
Américino played very well and won the championship.

06:37.560 --> 06:43.400
After the final, Don Dino looked at his son and smiled.

06:43.400 --> 06:49.480
"'You played a beautiful game, Dico,' he said.

06:49.480 --> 06:53.640
Vallemar Debrito.

06:53.640 --> 06:58.680
Baru Atletico liked Pele's beautiful game too.

06:58.680 --> 07:05.480
They wanted him for the club's new team of young players, Pacino.

07:05.480 --> 07:13.640
The team manager was Vallemar Debrito, a famous man in Brazilian soccer.

07:13.640 --> 07:17.320
Pele was very happy.

07:17.400 --> 07:22.440
Vallemar was a good manager and a good teacher.

07:22.440 --> 07:29.800
In 1953, Pacino won the Baru Young Team Championship.

07:29.800 --> 07:33.240
After this, Vallemar moved away.

07:33.240 --> 07:37.000
Pele was very sorry.

07:37.000 --> 07:44.200
One year later, Pele finished school and started to work in a shoe factory.

07:44.200 --> 07:50.120
At weekends, he played for Pacino, but he didn't like the new manager.

07:51.400 --> 07:54.680
1954 was a bad year.

07:56.040 --> 08:00.760
In the winter of the new year, Vallemar came to Pele's house.

08:01.640 --> 08:03.640
He wanted to talk to the family.

08:05.240 --> 08:08.200
"'Your son is 15 now,' he said.

08:08.920 --> 08:11.400
He's a very good soccer player.

08:12.360 --> 08:15.000
He can try for a job with Santos.

08:16.520 --> 08:18.760
Dondino and Pele were happy.

08:19.880 --> 08:23.400
Santos was a very famous club in Brazil.

08:24.840 --> 08:28.440
Celeste didn't like it, but she said, yes.

08:30.120 --> 08:35.960
Some days later, Dondino and Pele went to Santos on the train.

08:36.920 --> 08:41.880
"'The Santos players aren't going to like me,' Pele said.'

08:43.160 --> 08:45.080
But there was no problem.

08:45.960 --> 08:50.920
Pele played well, and the club was happy with its new player.

08:52.440 --> 08:54.200
Pele was happy too.

08:55.560 --> 08:59.640
After some weeks, he had a good friend on the team.

09:00.600 --> 09:02.360
His name was Zito.

09:03.240 --> 09:10.120
Pele wasn't in the first team, but one day, a first team player,

09:10.680 --> 09:13.480
Vasconcelos, had an injury.

09:15.480 --> 09:20.520
"'Let's put young Pele in the first team,' the manager said.

09:21.560 --> 09:26.200
Pele played well, and stayed in the first team.

09:27.160 --> 09:33.800
He scored his first goal for them on September 7th, 1956.

09:35.000 --> 09:39.080
After that, he started to score a lot of goals.

09:40.280 --> 09:42.280
The team were very happy.

09:43.960 --> 09:50.200
In June 1957, they played in the Maracanya Championship.

09:51.160 --> 09:53.800
Pele scored eight goals.

09:54.600 --> 09:57.400
Suddenly, he was famous.

09:58.600 --> 10:01.400
"'Thank you, Voldemort,' said Pele.

10:03.000 --> 10:04.600
The World Cup Games.

10:06.600 --> 10:09.800
"'Pele, Pele, Pele, Pele, Pele.'"

10:10.200 --> 10:12.200
Called the Brazilian soccer fans.

10:13.400 --> 10:17.000
The managers of the Brazilian team listened.

10:17.800 --> 10:25.960
Late in 1957, the names of the new Brazilian World Cup team were on the radio.

10:27.240 --> 10:33.960
Castillo, Gilmar, Matzola, Helle.

10:35.800 --> 10:36.920
"'Can that be right?'

10:37.800 --> 10:38.600
Pele asked.

10:39.480 --> 10:40.680
"'They want me?'"

10:42.440 --> 10:44.840
He was only 17.

10:47.240 --> 10:51.560
The 1958 World Cup Games were in Sweden.

10:52.520 --> 10:54.680
Pele played very well.

10:55.560 --> 10:59.320
Brazil won their first games with no problems.

11:00.520 --> 11:03.480
Then they beat Russia to nothing.

11:04.760 --> 11:06.680
But it was a difficult game.

11:08.280 --> 11:13.720
Wales were a strong team too, but Pele scored a goal.

11:14.440 --> 11:17.000
And Brazil won one nothing.

11:18.520 --> 11:21.000
The game with France wasn't difficult.

11:21.880 --> 11:23.960
Brazil won five too.

11:24.920 --> 11:28.120
And Pele scored three goals.

11:29.640 --> 11:32.280
Now they were in the final with Sweden.

11:33.800 --> 11:38.600
Brazil didn't start well, and Sweden scored first.

11:39.480 --> 11:43.480
But then, Brazil scored five goals.

11:44.920 --> 11:50.280
Two of those goals were Pele's and Brazil won five too.

11:51.880 --> 11:56.840
Pele scored six goals in his first World Cup.

11:58.120 --> 12:00.040
Brazil were the champions.

12:01.240 --> 12:04.520
Now Pele wasn't only famous in Brazil.

12:05.400 --> 12:12.040
Pele didn't play in the later games of the 1962 World Cup in Chile

12:12.040 --> 12:14.440
because he had an injury.

12:15.240 --> 12:22.120
He watched his team, and they beat Czechoslovakia 3-1 in the final.

12:23.080 --> 12:25.640
Brazil were the champions again.

12:26.200 --> 12:29.560
And Pele was very happy for the team.

12:29.560 --> 12:35.480
The 1966 World Cup was in England.

12:36.520 --> 12:39.720
Pele doesn't like remembering this championship.

12:41.000 --> 12:45.320
Usually, Brazil went to the games with 22 players.

12:46.120 --> 12:48.920
In England, they had 43.

12:50.200 --> 12:55.480
This was bad for the team because there were new players in every game.

12:56.280 --> 13:01.320
In an early game, Portugal beat them 3-1.

13:02.200 --> 13:06.280
The day after that game, Brazil went home.

13:08.440 --> 13:13.880
In 1970, the World Cup championship was in Mexico.

13:15.000 --> 13:21.400
Pele was only 29, but he was the old man of the Brazilian team.

13:22.040 --> 13:25.560
They beat Czechoslovakia or 1.

13:26.520 --> 13:30.120
Then they played England, the World Champions.

13:31.320 --> 13:37.480
It was a very interesting game, and Brazil won 1-0.

13:38.840 --> 13:46.360
After this, they beat Romania 3-2, and Pele scored two goals.

13:47.720 --> 13:51.000
Then they played Peru in the Jalisco Stadium.

13:51.480 --> 13:53.720
And they won 4-2.

13:55.000 --> 14:00.120
Now, there was only one game with Uruguay before the final.

14:01.160 --> 14:05.400
It was difficult, but Brazil won 3-1.

14:06.680 --> 14:12.280
The team went to Mexico City and waited for the final with Italy.

14:14.520 --> 14:19.880
The 1970 World Cup final started in the Aztec Stadium

14:19.880 --> 14:24.120
on the afternoon of June 21, 1970.

14:25.160 --> 14:28.280
Pele quickly scored a very good goal.

14:29.240 --> 14:35.160
There was a goal from Italy, but then Brazil scored 3 times.

14:36.120 --> 14:38.360
They won 4-1.

14:39.800 --> 14:44.440
After the game, Pele said goodbye to World Cup soccer.

14:45.640 --> 14:47.240
People were very sorry.

14:48.040 --> 14:53.160
How many players in the world can say I won 3 World Cups?

14:53.720 --> 14:54.280
They asked.

14:55.400 --> 14:57.240
There was only one answer.

14:58.040 --> 14:59.880
There was only one man.

15:00.840 --> 15:03.000
His name was Pele.

15:04.920 --> 15:06.120
A difficult girl.

15:08.280 --> 15:12.280
It was a Saturday night in 1958.

15:13.240 --> 15:16.280
Pele and Zito were in Santos again.

15:16.840 --> 15:18.120
After the World Cup.

15:19.800 --> 15:24.120
There's a girl's ball game in the stadium, Zito said.

15:24.920 --> 15:26.360
Let's go and watch.

15:28.520 --> 15:31.560
There was a young white girl at the ball game.

15:32.680 --> 15:37.000
She looked at Pele many times, and he looked at her.

15:38.840 --> 15:44.600
You're the famous Pele, and you play for Santos, she said, after the game.

15:45.400 --> 15:47.880
That's right, Pele said.

15:48.840 --> 15:50.360
Are you from the town?

15:52.040 --> 15:53.880
Yes, a girl said.

15:54.760 --> 15:56.840
But I don't like soccer.

15:58.120 --> 15:59.400
Then she walked away.

16:01.000 --> 16:01.960
Who was that?

16:02.840 --> 16:03.640
Zito asked.

16:05.160 --> 16:06.040
Pele smiled.

16:07.080 --> 16:09.560
A difficult girl, he said.

16:11.320 --> 16:13.720
Pele liked the difficult girl,

16:14.360 --> 16:16.200
but he didn't know her name.

16:17.880 --> 16:19.400
He talked to her friends.

16:21.080 --> 16:24.120
Her names, Rosemary Colby, they said.

16:25.000 --> 16:27.000
She works in a music store.

16:29.240 --> 16:32.760
That same week, Pele went to the store.

16:34.280 --> 16:36.040
Rosemary was there.

16:37.400 --> 16:41.480
They talked for some time, then Pele asked.

16:42.280 --> 16:45.160
Can you come out with me sometimes?

16:46.920 --> 16:49.720
I'm sorry, Rosemary said.

16:50.600 --> 16:52.040
I'm only 14.

16:53.000 --> 16:54.840
I don't go out with boys.

16:56.200 --> 16:58.920
But come to my house one afternoon.

17:01.000 --> 17:06.120
Pele was a visitor at Rosemary's house for seven years.

17:07.080 --> 17:12.920
Then, in February 1965, they married.

17:14.120 --> 17:20.200
The boy with no shoes and the difficult girl were very happy.

17:22.280 --> 17:24.040
Pele's years with Santos.

17:26.040 --> 17:34.680
Pele played for Santos from August 1956 to October 1974.

17:35.640 --> 17:42.120
In those years, they were the number one club in Brazil and the world.

17:43.240 --> 17:58.680
They won the Brazilian championship in 1961, 1962, 1963, 1964, and 1965.

17:59.480 --> 18:05.240
They won the South American club championship in 1962,

18:06.120 --> 18:10.760
1963, and 1968.

18:11.800 --> 18:16.600
And they won the world club championship in the same years.

18:18.280 --> 18:24.760
Pele and the Santos team visited many countries and played a lot of games.

18:25.560 --> 18:28.760
Sometimes this was difficult for Pele.

18:29.560 --> 18:32.920
He didn't like staying in hotels all the time.

18:33.640 --> 18:37.160
He wanted to be home in Brazil with his family.

18:38.600 --> 18:45.640
Pele's final game for Santos was on October 2nd, 1974.

18:46.760 --> 18:49.080
The game was with Pontipreta.

18:50.040 --> 18:53.720
After a short time, Pele stopped playing.

18:54.680 --> 18:59.560
He had the ball in his hands and looked at the fans in the stadium.

19:01.400 --> 19:05.800
Thank you, he said, and he walked away from the game.

19:07.560 --> 19:10.360
We love you, called the fans.

19:12.440 --> 19:19.960
After Santos, Pele went to New York for a job with an American team, New York Cosmos.

19:20.920 --> 19:26.040
The job was for $4,700,000.

19:27.560 --> 19:30.920
Many people in Brazil were unhappy about this.

19:32.040 --> 19:38.040
Pele is only going for the money, they said, but they were wrong.

19:39.320 --> 19:42.600
Pele wanted to make soccer famous in the US.

19:43.480 --> 19:47.240
He did this, and his new team were very happy.

19:47.480 --> 19:53.000
Pele stayed with New York Cosmos for three years.

19:53.960 --> 19:59.000
His final game was on October 1st, 1977.

20:00.040 --> 20:02.920
It was with his old club, Santos.

20:04.360 --> 20:08.440
Pele played for his new team and then for Santos.

20:09.160 --> 20:13.960
He scored a good goal and said goodbye to soccer.

20:13.960 --> 20:17.320
After soccer.

20:19.560 --> 20:21.560
Pele didn't stop working.

20:22.440 --> 20:28.520
He wasn't only a good soccer player and teacher, he loved young people too.

20:29.880 --> 20:36.760
He worked for UNICEF and talked with governments about the problems of the world's children.

20:37.400 --> 20:43.880
Then, in 1995, he started to work for the Brazilian government.

20:45.080 --> 20:50.840
But the world's soccer fans remember him for his two good feet and say,

20:51.720 --> 21:02.840
thank you Pele, soccer champion of the world.

